==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Plouter
<hw>Plout"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <altsp>[Also
<asp>plowter</asp>, <asp>plotter</asp>.]</altsp> <ety>[Perh.
imitative.]</ety> <def>To wade or move about with splashing; to dabble;
also, to potter; trifle; idle.</def> <mark>[Scot. & Dial.
Eng.]</mark></p>

<p><q>I did not want to <qex>plowter</qex> about any more.</q>
<rj><qau>Kipling.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Plouter</ent>⟦br⟧

